Explanation:

- I scanned the file app/lin/apidoc.py for constructs that bind HTTP request paths (literal strings like "/foo" or framework naming conventions that implicitly create paths) to handlers.
- No Flask route decorators (e.g., @app.route, @blueprint.route) or calls to app.add_url_rule are present in this file.
- The file defines helper classes and functions:
  - SpecTree.validate: a decorator factory for request/response validation. It does not itself bind any HTTP path — it augments handlers that are defined elsewhere.
  - schema_response(app) registers an app.after_request handler (make_schema_response) — this is a request lifecycle hook, not an API route bound to a path.
  - DocResponse, BaseModel, ValidationError, and related utilities are types used for validation/response handling, not route bindings.
- Therefore there are no API entries (no path → handler bindings) extractable from this source file. I did not include any speculative entries; per the instructions, only explicit path strings or framework-supported naming-convention-derived paths would be included.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.
path.title: Path

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.
handler.title: Handler

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
handler_in_same_file.title: Handler In Same File

path_is_prefix.title: Path Is Prefix

path_from_string_literal.description: Whether the path string is extracted from a literal string defined in the source code.
path_from_string_literal.title: Path From String Literal

path_from_naming_convention.description: Whether the path string is derived from a naming convention supported by the framework.
path_from_naming_convention.title: Path From Naming Convention
